'''Arabianus''' ({{lang-grc|Ἀραβιανὸς}}) was an eminent Christian writer who lived around 196 CE. He composed some books on Christian doctrine, which are lost.<ref>[[Eusebius]], ''[[Church History (Eusebius)|Church History]]'' v. 27</ref><ref>[[Jerome]], ''[[De Viris Illustribus (Jerome)|De Viris Illustribus]]'' c. 51</ref> Nothing more is known of him, and the writers who mention him, like [[Eusebius]], do not even tell us the title of the work Arabianus wrote.<ref>{{cite book | last =Schaff | first =Philip | authorlink =Philip Schaff | last2=Wace | first2=Henry | authorlink2=Henry Wace (priest) | title =A Select Library of Nicene and Post-Nicene Fathers of the Christian Church | publisher =[[Christian Literature Company]] | volume =2 | date =1890 | pages =245 | url =https://books.google.com/books?id=RdsIAQAAIAAJ | accessdate=2017-03-16}}</ref>

