'''Lou Rae''' is a Tasmanian author and historian of the [[West Coast of Tasmania]].

His publications have included articles about [[Rosebery, Tasmania]],<ref>{{Citation | author1=Rae, Lou | title=A window on Rosebery : a pictorial review of the 100 years in and around the environs of Rosebery on Tasmania's rugged West Coast, 1893-1993 | publication-date=1994 | publisher=L. Rae | isbn=978-0-9592098-4-6 }}</ref> the [[Emu Bay Railway]] <ref>{{Citation | author1=Rae, Lou | title=The Emu Bay Railway : VDL Company to Pasminco | publication-date=1991 | publisher=L. Rae | isbn=978-0-9592098-2-2 }}</ref> [[Queenstown, Tasmania]]<ref>http://pandora.nla.gov.au/nph-wb/20010403130000/http://www.federation100.tas.gov.au/writersprogram/writers/lou_rae.html</ref> and the [[Mount Lyell Railway]] otherwise known as the ''Abt Railway'',<ref>{{Citation | author1=Rae, Lou | title=The Mt Lyell Mining and Railway Co. Ltd : a pictorial history 1893-1993 | publication-date=1993 | publisher=L. Rae | isbn=978-0-9592098-3-9 }}</ref> as well as the Sandfly Colliery Tramway.<ref>{{Citation | author1=Rae, Lou. An introduction to the Sandfly colliery tramway | author2=Whitham, Lindsay. The Sandfly Coal Mine and tramway | author3=Chynoweth, R. Wayne. The locomotives of the Sandfly and Catamaran tramways | author4=Light Railway Research Society of Australia | title=Sandfly colliery tramway, Tasmania | publication-date=1988 | publisher=Light Railway Research Society of Australia | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/158847064 | accessdate=11 January 2014 }}</ref>

His publications about railways on the west coast of Tasmania have gone into multiple editions, as well as modifying for the changes in the fate of the railways.<ref>An example is the range of titles from 1988 to the 2010s about the Abt Railway</ref>

He also has been a postgraduate student at the [[University of Tasmania]], culminating in his 2005 PhD thesis about the Mount Lyell area.<ref>{{Citation | author1=Rae, Louis Gould | title=The lost province : exploration, isolation, innovation and domination in the Mount Lyell Region, 1859-1935 | publication-date=2005 | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/34479081 | accessdate=21 June 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | title=[Biographical cuttings on Lou Rae, author and historian, containing one or more cuttings from newspapers or journals] | publication-date=1900 | url=http://trove.nla.gov.au/work/35916585 | accessdate=11 January 2014 }}</ref>

His session at [[The Unconformity]] event in Queenstown in October 2016 addresses the issues of sources and historiography of the Western Tasmanian region.<ref>http://theunconformity.com.au/events/new-discoveries-old-traps-researching-west-coasts-past/</ref>

