'''Rolf Danielsen''' (19 October 1922 &ndash; 25 April 2002) was a Norwegian educator, author and historian.
He was born in [[Hammerfest]] in [[Finnmark]], Norway. He was awarded his [[cand.philol.]] from the [[University of Oslo]] (1950). Danielsen subsequently worked at the University of Oslo (1950-1951) and [[University of Gothenburg]] (1963-1964). He was a professor of modern history at the [[University of Bergen]] from 1968 to 1991.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Rolf Danielsen |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Rolf_Danielsen |language=Norwegian | accessdate=20 July 2011 }}</ref>
His thesis was a study on the [[Parliament of Norway]] ({{cite book|title=Tidsrommet 1870&ndash;1908|series=Det Norske Storting gjennom 150 år|volume=2}}). He has written volume four of the History of [[Trondheim]]. He was a board member of [[The Research Council of Norway]] (''Norges almenvitenskapelige forskningsråd'') from 1973 to 1975.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Rolf Danielsen |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Edgar |last=Hovland |authorlink= |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Rolf_Danielsen/utdypning|language=Norwegian |accessdate=20 July 2011}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.forskningsradet.no/no/Om_Forskningsradet/1138650413071|title= Om Noregs forskingsråd |publisher = Norges almenvitenskapelige forskningsråd|accessdate= January 1, 2017 }}</ref>
